lead_paragraph: Venus Williams climbed five spots to No. 9 in the rankings, meaning she and her sister No. 7 Serena are each in the top 10 for the first time in nearly two years. Justine Henin stayed at No. 1, and the United States Open runner-up Svetlana Kuznetsova moved up two places to No. 2. Maria Sharapova dropped to No. 4 from No. 2 after her title defense at Flushing Meadows ended with a third-round loss.
